  <a id="6190" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#6178" class="Function">VI</a> <a id="6193" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#6193" class="Bound">u</a> <a id="6195" class="Symbol">=</a> <a id="6197" href="NotionsOfDecidability.Decidable.html#410" class="Function">map-decidable</a> <a id="6211" class="Symbol">(</a><a id="6212" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#6041" class="Function">V</a> <a id="6214" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#6193" class="Bound">u</a><a id="6215" class="Symbol">)</a> <a id="6217" class="Symbol">(</a><a id="6218" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#5969" class="Function">IV</a> <a id="6221" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#6193" class="Bound">u</a><a id="6222" class="Symbol">)</a> <a id="6224" class="Symbol">(</a><a id="6225" href="UF.DiscreteAndSeparated.html#2183" class="Function">ℕ-is-discrete</a> <a id="6239" class="Symbol">(</a><a id="6240" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#4296" class="Bound">f</a> <a id="6242" class="Symbol">(</a><a id="6243" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#4514" class="Function">G</a> <a id="6245" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#6193" class="Bound">u</a><a id="6246" class="Symbol">))</a> <a id="6249" class="Symbol">(</a><a id="6250" href="TypeTopology.DecidabilityOfNonContinuity.html#4296" class="Bound">f</a> <a id="6252" href="CoNaturals.GenericConvergentSequence.html#5876" class="Function">∞</a><a id="6253" class="Symbol">))</a>

<a id="6257" class="Markup">\end{code}</a><a id="6267" class="Background">

In the following fact we can replace Σ by ∃ because WLPO is a
proposition. Hence WLPO is the propositional truncation of the type
Σ f ꞉ (ℕ∞ → ℕ) , ¬ continuous f.

</a><a id="6433" class="Markup">\begin{code}</a>

